cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses the security of Tor and other secure-communication networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the targeting of specific users on these networks, which involves network and information security (cs.NI). The paper presents a model of adversaries and investigates their behavior, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the selection of websites for targeting, which involves cybersecurity (cs.CY).
